# API Module Pattern

## Layer responsibilities
- **Controller**: HTTP only. Parse validated body, call service, return response. No business logic.
- **Service**: Business logic only. Throws typed errors. Never imports `req`/`res`.
- **Data access**: Prisma queries only. Always scoped by `tenantId`.

## Error handling
Throw typed errors in services. Let the centralized error middleware handle HTTP responses.

```typescript
// ✅ service.ts
if (!card) throw new NotFoundError('Card not found');

// ✅ controller.ts
const card = await cardService.getById(tenantId, id);
res.json(card);
```

Never catch errors in the controller just to re-throw or log — let middleware handle it.

## HTTP status codes (strict)
| Scenario | Code |
|---|---|
| POST (resource created) | 201 |
| GET / PATCH | 200 |
| DELETE | 204 |
| Validation failure | 400 |
| No/bad/expired token | 401 |
| Valid token, wrong tenant | 403 |
| Resource not found | 404 |

## Route shape
- Boards: `GET/POST /api/boards`, `GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/boards/:id`
- Lanes: `POST /api/boards/:boardId/lanes`, `PATCH/DELETE /api/lanes/:id`, `PATCH /api/lanes/reorder`
- Cards: `POST /api/lanes/:laneId/cards`, `PATCH/DELETE /api/cards/:id`, `PATCH /api/cards/move`
- Auth: `POST /api/auth/register`, `POST /api/auth/login`, `POST /api/auth/refresh`
